  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Malodor production is bacterial in origin. The bacterial activity of anaerobic bacteria
      results in the breakdown of proteins and the production of foul smelling compounds. The aim
      of the study is to test the hypothesis that bacterial growth on dental implants contributes
      to malodor production and to see whether this contribution is associated with various
      properties of the dental implant such as: maker, type, depth ext.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
